<h3>System Usage Guide</h3>

<p>
    This guide helps new staff members understand how to operate the Ocean View Resort Reservation System efficiently.
</p>

<hr>

<h4>1. Creating a Reservation</h4>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <b>Reservations → Add Reservation</b>.</li>
    <li>Enter guest details.</li>
    <li>Select room type and available room.</li>
    <li>Choose check-in and check-out dates.</li>
    <li>Click <b>Create Reservation</b>.</li>
</ol>

<p>
    The system automatically checks room availability and prevents double booking.
</p>

<hr>

<h4>2. Managing Reservations</h4>

<ul>
    <li>Use <b>View Reservations</b> to see all reservations.</li>
    <li>You can edit reservation details if needed.</li>
    <li>You may delete incorrect reservations.</li>
    <li>The system shows reservation status.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h4>3. Generating Bills</h4>

<ol>
    <li>Open <b>View Reservations</b>.</li>
    <li>Select <b>Generate Bill</b>.</li>
    <li>Review the invoice.</li>
    <li>Select payment method.</li>
    <li>Click <b>Pay Bill</b>.</li>
</ol>

<p>
    Once payment is completed:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>The reservation status updates to <b>PAID</b>.</li>
    <li>The invoice is stored in the billing records.</li>
    <li>A receipt is generated.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h4>4. Reports and Monitoring</h4>

The <b>Reports</b> section provides management insights:

<ul>
    <li>Total revenue</li>
    <li>Reservation statistics</li>
    <li>Revenue by room type</li>
</ul>

These reports assist management in decision-making and operational planning.

<hr>

<h4>5. Web Service APIs</h4>

The system also exposes machine-readable APIs:

<ul>
    <li><b>/api/reservations</b></li>
    <li><b>/api/bills</b></li>
    <li><b>/api/reports/revenue</b></li>
</ul>

These APIs allow integration with other systems or external applications.

<hr>

<h4>6. Security and Access</h4>

<ul>
    <li>Only authenticated staff can access the system.</li>
    <li>Sessions automatically protect dashboard access.</li>
    <li>Users must log out after completing their work.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

